{
  "texts": [
    "These results suggest that the domains of reflective practice including reflection-on-action; reflection with others and selfappraisal all improved, while the domain of reflection-in-action still needs to be enhanced.",
    "We compared the data collected from each survey to investigate variations due to sex.",
    "Associations with sex are shown in Tables 3 and 4.",
    "Prior to teaching; for question Q8 \"After interacting with patients I wonder about my own experience of the interaction\", a significantly higher percentage of females chose \"definitely agree\" (n = 17, 56.6%, p = 0.032).",
    "There was no statistical difference between other questions in pre-or post-session surveys."
  ]
}